HEADWORD: Coagulum
<hw>Co*ag"u*lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Coagula</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. See <er>Coagulate</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>The thick, curdy precipitate formed by the
coagulation of albuminous matter; any mass of coagulated matter, as a
clot of blood.</def>⟦br⟧
